Hog-raising is the business of Severo G.. He is married to Patrocinia and they are blessed with five children who are at different levels of educational attainment: Aries, 29 years old, is a college graduate and now a policeman; 
Ariel, 27 years old, is also a college graduate; 
April, 26 years old, is a college graduate and now works as an Overseas Filipino worker in Ireland; 
Severo III, 23 years old, is a college graduate and also a policeman, like his older brother; and 
Almer, 18 years old, is currently enrolled in college, taking Criminology. 

Currently their expenses include the allowance, tuition and projects of their youngest son. So, the couple is striving hard to earn a higher income to accommodate the needs of their youngest son. Severo would like to apply for this loan, amounting to PHP 5,000, for his hog-raising business. He is hoping that his request will be granted for the development of his hog-raising business.
